FBIS3-419 "drafr044_c_94027" FBIS-AFR-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Ramaphosa Calls for Disbanding ISD MB0603143294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1311 GMT 6 Mar 94 MB0603143294 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Durban March 6 SAPA -- African National Congress [ANC] Secretary General Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday [6 March] called for the disbanding of the SA Police's Internal Stability Division [ISD]. Reacting to the killing of 11 people in Bhambayi north of Durban on Saturday evening, Mr Ramaphosa claimed the ISD was responsible for the death of thousands of people throughout the country. The ANC would not only demand the withdrawal of the ISD from the townships, but that it be completely disbanded, he said. Mr Ramaphosa and other regional ANC leaders were to visit Bhambayi on Sunday afternoon.
